#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:9
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid "gzip"
msgstr "Guhingura ingano"

#. Tag: author
#: index.docbook:12
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid "&Lauri.Watts; &Lauri.Watts.mail;"
msgstr ". ; . . Ibaruwa ; "

#. Tag: trans_comment
#: index.docbook:13
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid "ROLES_OF_TRANSLATORS"
msgstr "IZINA RY'ABAVUNUZI"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:17
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid "<command>gzip</command> is a compression program"
msgstr "<command> </command> ni A igabanyangano Porogaramu "

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:19
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The gzip KIO worker is not directly usable, and is intended for use as a "
"filter. For example, the tar KIO worker can filter a file through the gzip "
"KIO worker, in order to display the contents of a <literal role=\"extension"
"\">tar.gz</literal> file directly in a &konqueror; window."
msgstr ""
"ni OYA , na ni ya:  Koresha Nka A Akayunguruzo: . Urugero: , i Akayunguruzo: "
"A Idosiye Gihinguranya i , in Itondekanya Kuri Kugaragaza: i Ibigize Bya A "
"<literal role=\"extension\"> . </literal> Idosiye in A &konqueror; "
"Idirishya . "

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:25
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you click on a file compressed with a <literal role=\"extension\">gz</"
"literal> extension in &konqueror;, this KIO worker is used to uncompress it "
"and display it as a normal (uncompressed) file."
msgstr ""
"Kanda ku A Idosiye Byegeranijwe Na: A <literal role=\"extension\"> </"
"literal> Umugereka: in &konqueror; , iyi ni Byakoreshejwe Kuri na "
"Kugaragaza: Nka A Bisanzwe ( Birekuye ) Idosiye . "

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:30
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you are a developer, and would like to use the gzip filter, you can find "
"documentation on using KIO workers at <ulink url=\"http://techbase.kde.org"
"\">http://techbase.kde.org</ulink>"
msgstr "kde."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:34
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid "See the manual: <ulink url=\"man:/gzip\">gzip</ulink>."
msgstr "i Bikorwa : <ulink url=\"man:/gzip\"> </ulink> . "
